{
    "chapter": 75,
    "verses": {
        "1": {
            "verses": {
                "75:1": {
                    "id": 1
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Nay! (the l is extra in both instances) I swear by the Day of Resurrection.</p>"
        },
        "2": {
            "verses": {
                "75:2": {
                    "id": 2
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>And, nay, I swear by the (self-)reproaching soul, the one that reproaches itself, even if it should expend great effort in being virtuous (the response to the oath has been omitted, that is to say, la-tub`athunna, `you shall indeed be resurrected!', as indicated by [what follows]):</h2>"
        },
        "3": {
            "verses": {
                "75:3": {
                    "id": 3
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Does man, that is, [does] the disbeliever, suppose that We shall not assemble his bones?, for the raising [from the graves] and [for] the bringing back to life.</p>"
        },
        "4": {
            "verses": {
                "75:4": {
                    "id": 4
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Yes, indeed!, We shall assemble them. We are able, in addition to assembling them, to reshape [even] his fingers, that is to say, to restore their bones just as they had been, despite their smallness: so how much more so [are We able to restore] the larger ones!</p>"
        },
        "5": {
            "verses": {
                "75:5": {
                    "id": 5
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>Nay, but man desires to deny (li-yafjura: the lm is extra, and the subjunctive mood is because of an implied [preceding] an, `that') what lies ahead of him, namely, the Day of Resurrection, as is indicated by:</h2>"
        },
        "6": {
            "verses": {
                "75:6": {
                    "id": 6
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>He asks, `When is the Day of Resurrection?' — the question is meant in mockery and denial.</p>"
        },
        "7": {
            "verses": {
                "75:7": {
                    "id": 7
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>But when the eyes are dazzled (read bariqa or baraqa), startled and perplexed upon seeing some of those things which it used to deny;</p>"
        },
        "8": {
            "verses": {
                "75:8": {
                    "id": 8
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and the moon is eclipsed, darkening, its light disappearing,</p>"
        },
        "9": {
            "verses": {
                "75:9": {
                    "id": 9
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and the sun and the moon are brought together, so that both of them will rise from the west; or [it means when] the light of both of them disappears — and this will be on the Day of Resurrection —</p>"
        },
        "10": {
            "verses": {
                "75:10": {
                    "id": 10
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>on that day man will say, `Where is the escape?'</h2>"
        },
        "11": {
            "verses": {
                "75:11": {
                    "id": 11
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>No indeed! — a deterrent against seeking to escape — There is no refuge, no shelter to seek protection in.</p>"
        },
        "12": {
            "verses": {
                "75:12": {
                    "id": 12
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>On that day the recourse will be to your Lord, the [final] recourse of all creatures, whereupon they will be reckoned with and requited.</p>"
        },
        "13": {
            "verses": {
                "75:13": {
                    "id": 13
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>On that day man will be informed of what he has sent ahead and left behind, [he will be informed] of the his first and last deeds.</p>"
        },
        "14": {
            "verses": {
                "75:14": {
                    "id": 14
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Rather man has insight into his [own] soul, for his limbs will speak of his deeds (the h' [sc. the t' marbta in basratun] is for hyperbole), and so he must be requited,</p>"
        },
        "15": {
            "verses": {
                "75:15": {
                    "id": 15
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>though he should offer his excuses (ma`dhr is the plural of ma`dhira, but following a different pattern [from the usual ma`dhira, ma`dhir]) that is to say, whatever excuse he offers will not be accepted from him.</p>"
        },
        "16": {
            "verses": {
                "75:16": {
                    "id": 16
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>God, exalted be He, says to His Prophet: Do not move your tongue with it, with the Qur'n, before Gabriel is through with [reciting] it, to hasten it, fearing to lose it.</p>"
        },
        "17": {
            "verses": {
                "75:17": {
                    "id": 17
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Assuredly it is for Us to bring it together, in your breast, and to recite it, your reciting of it, that is, its flowing off your tongue.</p>"
        },
        "18": {
            "verses": {
                "75:18": {
                    "id": 18
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>So, when We recite it, to you, by means of Gabriel's recital, follow its recitation, listen to its recitation: thus the Prophet (s) would listen to it and then repeat it.</p>"
        },
        "19": {
            "verses": {
                "75:19": {
                    "id": 19
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Then, it is for Us to explain it, by making you comprehend [it]: the connection between this verse and what preceded [it] is that those [verses before] imply turning away from God's signs, whereas this one implies applying oneself to them by memorising them.</p>"
        },
        "20": {
            "verses": {
                "75:20": {
                    "id": 20
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>No indeed! (kall is for commencement, with the sense of al) Rather you love the transitory [life], this world (both verbs [here and below] may be read in the second or third person plural),</p>"
        },
        "21": {
            "verses": {
                "75:21": {
                    "id": 21
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and forsake the Hereafter, thus neglecting to work towards [attaining bliss in] it.</p>"
        },
        "22": {
            "verses": {
                "75:22": {
                    "id": 22
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Some faces on that day, that is, on the Day of Resurrection, will be radiant, fair and resplendent,</p>"
        },
        "23": {
            "verses": {
                "75:23": {
                    "id": 23
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>looking upon their Lord, in other words, they will see God, glorified and exalted be He, in the Hereafter.</p>"
        },
        "24": {
            "verses": {
                "75:24": {
                    "id": 24
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>And other faces on that day will be scowling, glowering, frowning terribly,</p>"
        },
        "25": {
            "verses": {
                "75:25": {
                    "id": 25
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>certain that a spine-crushing calamity will fall on them, a great catastrophe, one that `crushes the spine' (fiqr).</p>"
        },
        "26": {
            "verses": {
                "75:26": {
                    "id": 26
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>No indeed! (kall: in the sense of al) When it, the soul, reaches up to the collar bones,</p>"
        },
        "27": {
            "verses": {
                "75:27": {
                    "id": 27
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and it is said, [and] those around him [the dying one] say: `Where is the enchanter?', to perform incantations on him and cure him,</p>"
        },
        "28": {
            "verses": {
                "75:28": {
                    "id": 28
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and he suspects, [he] the one whose soul has reached this [stage], that it is the [time of] parting, the parting with this world,</p>"
        },
        "29": {
            "verses": {
                "75:29": {
                    "id": 29
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and the shank is intertwined with the [other] shank, that is, one of his shanks [will be intertwined] with his other shank at the moment of death; or [it means] the distress of parting with this world is intertwined with the distress of the arrival of the Hereafter;</p>"
        },
        "30": {
            "verses": {
                "75:30": {
                    "id": 30
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>on that day to your Lord will be the driving [of the souls] (al-masq means al-sawq; this indicates the operator of the [above] idh, `when', the meaning being: `when the soul reaches the throat, it will be driven towards the judgement of its Lord').</p>"
        },
        "31": {
            "verses": {
                "75:31": {
                    "id": 31
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>For he, man, neither affirmed [the truth] nor prayed,</h2>"
        },
        "32": {
            "verses": {
                "75:32": {
                    "id": 32
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>but he denied, the Qur'n, and he turned away, from faith,</h2>"
        },
        "33": {
            "verses": {
                "75:33": {
                    "id": 33
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>then went off to his family swaggering, strutting about in self-conceit.</p>"
        },
        "34": {
            "verses": {
                "75:34": {
                    "id": 34
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>[Woe be] nearer to you (there is a shift from the third [to the second] person address here; the term [awl] is a noun of action, with the [following] lm being explicative, in other words, `what you are averse to is [now] near to you') and nearer, that is because you are more deserving of it [woe] than anyone else,</p>"
        },
        "35": {
            "verses": {
                "75:35": {
                    "id": 35
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>then [may woe be] nearer to you and nearer! — [repeated] for emphasis.</p>"
        },
        "36": {
            "verses": {
                "75:36": {
                    "id": 36
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Does man suppose that he is to be left aimless?, left to his own devices without being obligated to the [prescribed] laws: let him not suppose that!</p>"
        },
        "37": {
            "verses": {
                "75:37": {
                    "id": 37
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Was he not — that is, [indeed] he was — a drop of emitted semen? (read yumn or tumn) deposited into the womb.</p>"
        },
        "38": {
            "verses": {
                "75:38": {
                    "id": 38
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Then it, the drop of semen, became a clot; then He, God, created, from it man, and proportioned [him], making the parts of his body upright,</p>"
        },
        "39": {
            "verses": {
                "75:39": {
                    "id": 39
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and made of it, of the drop of semen that became a blood-clot, then an embryo, a [small] mass of flesh, the two sexes, the two kinds, the male and the female, at times coming together and at times each being on their own.</p>"
        },
        "40": {
            "verses": {
                "75:40": {
                    "id": 40
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Is not such, a Doer of [all] these things, able to revive the dead? — the Prophet (s) would say, `Yes, indeed!' Meccan or Medinese, consisting of 31 verses.</p>"
        }
    }
}